649]},{"content":"If a device was activated with a Microsoft account, the MDM system would not be able to block that account from being used.","pos":[31650,31773]},{"content":"Allow Adding Non Microsoft Accounts","pos":[31778,31813]},{"content":"Specifies whether users are allowed to add email accounts other than Microsoft accounts after MDM enrollment.","pos":[31816,31925]},{"content":"If <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Allow Microsoft Account<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> is applied, user can also not use a Microsoft account.","pos":[31926,32011]},{"content":"Allow “Your Account”","pos":[32016,32036]},{"pos":[32039,32157],"content":"Specifies whether users are able to change account configuration in the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Your Email and Accounts<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> panel in Settings."},{"pos":[32197,32221],"content":"Device lock restrictions"},{"content":"It’s common sense to lock a device when it is not in use.","pos":[32223,32280]},{"content":"Microsoft recommends that you secure Windows 10 Mobile devices and implement a device lock policy.","pos":[32281,32379]},{"content":"A device password or PIN lock is a best practice for securing apps and data on devices.","pos":[32380,32467]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Windows Hello<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=723994)</ept> is the name given to the new biometric sign-in option that allows users to use their face, iris, or fingerprints to unlock their compatible device, all of which Windows 10 supports.","pos":[32468,32714]},{"pos":[32717,32907],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Note:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>  In addition to the device lock restrictions discussed in this section, Windows 10 supports Microsoft Passport for Work, which lets you access apps and services without a password."},{"content":"Table 6 lists the MDM settings in Windows 10 Mobile that you can use to configure device lock restrictions.","pos":[32910,33017]},{"content":"Table 6.","pos":[33019,33027]},{"content":"Windows 10 Mobile