hentication in <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>APN authentication type","pos":[70702,70844]},{"content":"Password","pos":[70899,70907]},{"content":"The password for the user account specified in <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>User name","pos":[70930,70994]},{"content":"Integrated circuit card ID","pos":[71050,71076]},{"content":"The integrated circuit card ID associated with the cellular connection profile","pos":[71099,71177]},{"pos":[71238,71258],"content":"Data leak protection"},{"content":"Some user experiences can risk corporate data stored on corporate devices.","pos":[71260,71334]},{"content":"For example, allowing users to copy and paste information out of the organization’s LOB app can put data at risk.","pos":[71335,71448]},{"content":"To mitigate the risk, you can restrict the Windows 10 Mobile user experience to help protect corporate data and prevent data leaks.","pos":[71449,71581]},{"content":"For example, you can prevent settings synchronization, copy-and-paste operations, and screen captures.","pos":[71582,71684]},{"content":"Table 16 lists the MDM settings in Windows 10 Mobile that you can use to help prevent data leaks.","pos":[71685,71782]},{"content":"Table 16.","pos":[71784,71793]},{"content":"Windows 10 Mobile data leak protection settings","pos":[71794,71841]},{"content":"Setting","pos":[71845,71852]},{"content":"Description","pos":[71892,71903]},{"content":"Allow copy and paste","pos":[72381,72401]},{"content":"Whether users can copy and paste content","pos":[72428,72468]},{"content":"Allow Cortana","pos":[72649,72662]},{"content":"Whether users can use Cortana on the device, where available","pos":[72696,72756]},{"content":"Allow device discovery","pos":[72917,72939]},{"content":"Whether the device discovery user experience is available on the lock screen (For example, this setting can control whether a device could discover a projector <ph id=\"ph1\">\\[</ph>or other devices<ph id=\"ph2\">\\]</ph> when the lock screen is displayed.)","pos":[72964,73180]},{"content":"Allow input personalization","pos":[73185,73212]},{"content":"Whether personally identifiable information can leave the device or be saved locally (for example, Cortana learning, inking, dictation)","pos":[73232,73367]},{"content":"Allow manual MDM unenrollment","pos":[73453,73482]},{"content":"Whether users are allowed to delete the workplace account (in other words, unenroll the device from the MDM system)","pos":[73500,73615]},{"content":"Allow screen capture","pos":[73721,73741]},{"content":"Whether users are allowed to capture screenshots on the device","pos":[73768,73830]},{"content":"Allow SIM error dialog prompt","pos":[73989,74018]},{"content":"Specifies whether to display a dialog prompt when no SIM card is installed","pos":[74036,74110]},{"content":"Allow sync my settings","pos":[74257,74279]},{"content":"Whether the user experience settings are synchronized between devices (works with Microsoft accounts only)","pos":[74304,74410]},{"content":"Allow toasts notifications above lock screen","pos":[74525,74569]},{"content":"Whether users are able to view toast notification on the device lock screen","pos":[74572,74647]},{"content":"Allow voice recording","pos":[74793,74814]},{"content":"Whether users are allowed to perform voice recordings.","pos":[74840,74894]},{"pos":[75093,75111],"content":"Storage management"},{"content":"Protecting the apps and data stored on a device is critical to device security.","pos":[75113,75192]},{"content":"One method for helping protect your apps and data is to encrypt internal device storage by using the device encryption in Windows 10 Mobile.","pos":[75193,75333]},{"content":"This encryption helps protect corporate data against unauthorized access, even when an unauthorized user has physical possession of the device.","pos":[75334,75477]},{"content":"A feature in Windows 10 Mobile is the ability to install apps on a secure digital (SD) card.","pos":[75479,75571]},{"content":"The operating system stores apps on a partition specifically designated for that purpose.","pos":[75572,75661]},{"content":"This feature is always on, so you don’t need to set a policy explicitly to enable it.","pos":[75662,75747]},{"content":"The SD card is uniquely paired with a device.","pos":[75748,75793]},{"content":"No other devices can see the apps or data on the encrypted partition, but they can access the data stored on the unencrypted partition of the SD card, such as music or photos.","pos":[75794,75969]},{"content":"You can disable the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Allow Storage Card<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> setting to prevent users from using SD cards altogether, but the primary advantage of the SD card app partition–encryption feature is that organizations can give users the flexibility to use an SD card while still protecting the confidential apps and data on it.","pos":[75970,76275]},{"content":"If you don’t encrypt storage, you can help protect your corporate apps and data by using the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Restrict app data to the system volume<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Restrict apps to the system volume<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> settings.","pos":[76277,76465]},{"content":"They help ensure that users cannot copy your apps and data to SD cards.","pos":[76466,76537]},{"content":"Table 17 lists the MDM storage-management settings that Windows 10 Mobile provides.","pos":[76539,76622]},{"content":"Table 17.","pos":[76624,76633]},{"content":"Windows 10 Mobile storage management settings","pos":[76634,76679]},{"content":"Setting","pos":[76797,76804]},{"content":"Description","pos":[76827,76838]},{"content":"Allow Storage Card","pos":[76901,76919]},{"content":"Whether users can use storage cards for device storage (This setting does not prevent programmatic access to the storage cards.)","pos":[76942,77070]},{"content":"Require Device Encryption","pos":[77117,77142]},{"content":"Whether internal storage is encrypted (When a device is encrypted, you cannot use a policy to turn encryption off.)","pos":[77165,77280]},{"content":"Encryption method","pos":[77326,77343]},{"content":"Specifies the BitLocker drive encryption method and cipher strength; can be one of the following values:","pos":[77366,77470]},{"content":"AES-Cipher Block Chaining (CBC) 128-bit","pos":[77483,77522]},{"content":"AES-CBC 256-bit","pos":[77539,77554]},{"content":"XEX-based tweaked-codebook mode with cipher text stealing (XTS)–AES (XTS-AES) 128-bit (this is the default)","pos":[77571,77678]},{"content":"XTS-AES-256-bit","pos":[77695,77710]},{"content":"Allow Federal Information Processing Standard (FIPS) algorithm policy","pos":[77772,77841]},{"content":"Whether the device allows or disallows the FIPS algorithm policy","pos":[77864,77928]},{"content":"SSL cipher suites","pos":[77974,77991]},{"content":"Specifies a list of the allowed cryptographic cipher algorithms for SSL connections","pos":[78014,78097]},{"content":"Restrict app data to the system volume","pos":[78144,78182]},{"content":"Specifies whether app data is restricted to the system drive","pos":[78205,78265]},{"content":"Restrict apps to the system volume","pos":[78311,78345]},{"content":"Specifies whether apps are restricted to the system drive","pos":[78368,78425]},{"pos":[78498,78512],"content":"App management"},{"content":"Apps help improve user productivity on mobile devices.","pos":[78514,78568]},{"content":"New to Windows 10 is the ability for organizations purchase apps from Windows Store for their employees and deploy those apps from Windows Store or an MDM system.","pos":[78569,78731]},{"content":"App management is becoming a key capability of MDM systems, helping reduce the effort required to perform common app-related tasks, such as distributing apps, and protecting data through app policies.","pos":[78732,78932]},{"content":"This section describes the app management features in Windows 10 Mobile and includes the following topics:","pos":[78933,79039]},{"content":"Universal Windows Platform (UWP)","pos":[79046,79078]},{"content":"Sourcing the right app","pos":[79091,79113]},{"content":"Windows Store for Business","pos":[79131,79157]},{"content":"Mobile application management (MAM) policies","pos":[79172,79216]},{"content":"Microsoft Edge","pos":[79229,79243]},{"pos":[79281,79307],"content":"Universal Windows Platform"},{"content":"Windows 10 introduces UWP, converging the application platform for all devices running some edition of Windows 10.","pos":[79309,79423]},{"content":"UWP apps run without modification on all editions of Windows 10, and Windows Store now has apps that you can license and purchased for all your Windows 10 devices.","pos":[79424,79587]},{"content":"Windows Phone 8.1 and Windows 8.1 apps still run on Windows 10 devices, but the MAM improvements in Windows 10 work only with UWP apps.","pos":[79588,79723]},{"content":"See the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Guide to Universal Windows Platform (UWP) apps<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=734056)</ept> for additional information.","pos":[79724,79857]},{"pos":[79892,79914],"content":"Sourcing the right app"},{"content":"The first step in app management is to obtain the apps your users need, and you can now acquire apps from Windows Store.","pos":[79916,80036]},{"content":"Developers can also create apps specific to an organization, known as <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>line-of-business (LOB) apps<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> (the developers of these apps are <bpt id=\"p2\">*</bpt>LOB publishers<ept id=\"p2\">*</ept>).","pos":[80037,80189]},{"content":"An LOB developer (internal or external) can now publish these apps to Windows Store at your request, or you can obtain the app packages offline and distribute them through your MDM system.","pos":[80190,80378]},{"content":"To install Windows Store or LOB apps, use the Windows Store cloud service or your MDM system to distribute the app packages.","pos":[80380,80504]},{"content":"Your MDM system can deploy apps online by redirecting the user to a licensed app in Windows Store or offline by distributing a package that you downloaded from Windows Store (also called <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>sideloading<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>) on Windows 10 Mobile devices.","pos":[80505,80736]},{"content":"You can fully automate the app deployment process so that no user intervention is required.","pos":[80737,80828]},{"content":"IT administrators can obtain apps through Store for Business.","pos":[80830,80891]},{"content":"Most apps can be distributed online, meaning that the user must be logged in to the device with an Azure AD account and have Internet access at the time of installation.","pos":[80892,81061]},{"content":"To distribute an app offline, the developer must opt in.","pos":[81062,81118]},{"content":"If the app developer doesn’t allow download of the app from Windows Store, then you must obtain the files directly from the developer or use the online method.","pos":[81119,81278]},{"content":"See <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Windows Store for Business<ept id=\"p1\">](windows-store-for-business.md)</ept> for additional information about apps obtained through Store for Business.","pos":[81279,81417]},{"content":"Windows Store apps are automatically trusted.","pos":[81418,81463]},{"content":"For custom LOB apps developed internally or by a trusted software vendor, ensure that the device trusts the app signing certificate.","pos":[81464,81596]},{"content":"There are two ways to establish this trust: use a signing certificate from a trusted source, or generate your own signing certificate and add your chain of trust to the trusted certificates on the device.","pos":[81597,81801]},{"content":"You can install up to 20 self-signed apps on a Windows 10 Mobile device.","pos":[81802,81874]},{"content":"When you purchase a signing certificate from a public CA, you can install more than 20 apps on a device, although you can install more than 20 self-signed apps per device with <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Windows 10 Mobile Enterprise<ept id=\"p1\">](#mobile-edition)</ept>.","pos":[81875,82099]},{"content":"Users can install apps from Windows Store that the organization purchases through the Store app on their device.","pos":[82101,82213]},{"content":"If you allow your users to log in with a Microsoft account, the Store app on the device provides a unified method for installing personal and corporate apps.","pos":[82214,82371]},{"pos":[82403,82421],"content":"Store for Business"},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Windows Store for Business<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=722910)</ept> is a web portal that IT pros and purchasers use to find, acquire, manage, and distribute apps to Windows 10 devices.","pos":[82423,82617]},{"content":"This online portal gives Azure AD authenticated managers access to Store for Business functionality and settings.","pos":[82618,82731]},{"content":"Store managers can create a private section of Windows Store in which organizations can manage apps specific and private to them.","pos":[82732,82861]},{"content":"Store for Business allows organizations to make apps available to their users and purchase app licenses for them.","pos":[82862,82975]},{"content":"They can also integrate their Store for Business subscriptions with their MDM systems, so the MDM system can deploy apps from their free Store for Business subscription.","pos":[82976,83145]},{"content":"The process for using Store for Business is as follows:","pos":[83147,83202]},{"content":"Create a Store for Business subscription for your organization.","pos":[83208,83271]},{"content":"In the Store for Business portal, acquire apps from Windows Store (only free apps are available at this time).","pos":[83276,83386]},{"content":"In Store for Business, distribute apps to users, and manage the app licenses for the apps acquired in the previous step.","pos":[83391,83511]},{"content":"Integrate your MDM system with your organization’s Store for Business subscription.","pos":[83516,83599]},{"content":"Use your MDM system to deploy the apps.","pos":[83604,83643]},{"pos":[83645,83756],"content":"For more information about Store for Business, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Windows Store for Business<ept id=\"p1\">](windows-store-for-business.md)</ept>."},{"pos":[83786,83830],"content":"Mobile application management (MAM) policies"},{"content":"With MDM, you can manage Device Guard on Windows 10 Mobile and create an allow (whitelist) or deny (blacklist) list of apps.","pos":[83832,83956]},{"content":"This capability extends to built-in apps, as well, such as phone, text messaging, email, and calendar.","pos":[83957,84059]},{"content":"The ability to allow or deny apps helps to ensure that people use their mobile devices for their intended purposes.","pos":[84060,84175]},{"content":"You can also control users’ access to Windows Store and whether the Store service updates apps automatically.","pos":[84177,84286]},{"content":"You can manage all these capabilities through your MDM system.","pos":[84287,84349]},{"content":"Table 18 lists the Windows 10 Mobile app management settings.","pos":[84350,84411]},{"content":"Table 18.","pos":[84413,84422]},{"content":"Windows 10 Mobile app management settings","pos":[84423,84464]},{"content":"Setting","pos":[84468,84475]},{"content":"Description","pos":[84517,84528]},{"content":"Allow All Trusted Apps","pos":[84936,84958]},{"content":"Whether users can sideload apps on the device","pos":[84985,85030]},{"content":"Allow App Store Auto Update","pos":[85170,85197]},{"content":"Whether automatic updates of apps from Windows Store are allowed","pos":[85219,85283]},{"content":"Allow Developer Unlock","pos":[85404,85426]},{"content":"Whether developer unlock is allowed","pos":[85453,85488]},{"content":"Allow Shared User App Data","pos":[85638,85664]},{"content":"Whether multiple users of the same app can share data","pos":[85687,85740]},{"content":"Allow Store","pos":[85872,85883]},{"content":"Whether Windows Store app is allowed to run","pos":[85921,85964]},{"content":"Allow Windows Bridge For Android App Execution","pos":[86106,86152]},{"content":"Whether the Windows Bridge for Android app is allowed to run","pos":[86155,86215]},{"content":"Application Restrictions","pos":[86340,86364]},{"content":"An XML blob that defines the app restrictions for a device (The XML blob can contain an app allow or deny list.","pos":[86389,86500]},{"content":"You can allow or deny apps based on their app ID or publisher.)","pos":[86501,86564]},{"content":"Require Private Store Only","pos":[86574,86600]},{"content":"Whether the private store is exclusively available to users (If enabled, only the private store is available.","pos":[86623,86732]},{"content":"If disabled, the retail catalog and private store are both available.)","pos":[86733,86803]},{"content":"Restrict App Data To System Volume","pos":[86808,86842]},{"content":"Whether app data is allowed only on the system drive","pos":[86857,86909]},{"content":"Restrict App To System Volume","pos":[87042,87071]},{"content":"Whether app installation is allowed only to the system drive","pos":[87091,87151]},{"content":"Start screen layout","pos":[87276,87295]},{"pos":[87325,87494],"content":"An XML blob used to configure the Start screen (See <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Start layout for Windows 10 Mobile editions<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=734057)</ept> for more information.)"},{"content":"One potential security issue is that users can register as Windows 10 Mobile app developers and turn on developer features on their device, potentially installing apps from unknown sources and opening the device to malware threats.","pos":[87510,87741]},{"content":"To prevent users from turning on developer features on their devices, set the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Disable development unlock (side loading)<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> policy, which you can configure through your MDM system.","pos":[87742,87922]},{"pos":[87953,87967],"content":"Microsof